family: Rosaceae
contains salicylic acid (precursor to aspirin)
generally safe
broadly anti-inflammatory&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;may be particularly helpful for gut pain
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;soothing on gut&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;chronic or acute gastrointestinal pain
methyl salicylate content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;results in slight wintergreen smell
preparation:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;tea&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;tincture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;glycerite
parts used:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;leaves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;inflorescence
not native to North America
7songsevensong suggests combining meadowsweet, catnip, chamomile, fennel in equal parts for GI pain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
